## ğŸ³ Dockerfile Best Practices

### 1. Use Specific Base Image Tags
**Rule:** Never use `latest` tag in production Dockerfiles.
```dockerfile
# âŒ Bad
FROM node:latest

# âœ… Good
FROM node:22-alpine
```

### 2. Leverage Layer Caching
**Rule:** Copy dependency files before source code.
```dockerfile
# âœ… Good - dependencies cached separately
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci
COPY . .
RUN npm run build
```

### 3. Use .dockerignore
**Rule:** Always include `.dockerignore` to exclude unnecessary files.
```dockerignore
node_modules
.git
.env
*.log
dist
coverage
```

### 4. Minimize Layers
**Rule:** Combine RUN commands to reduce image layers.
```dockerfile
# âŒ Bad - multiple layers
RUN apt-get update
RUN apt-get install -y curl
RUN apt-get clean

# âœ… Good - single layer
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y curl && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
```

### 5. Non-root User
**Rule:** Always run containers as non-root user.
```dockerfile
RUN addgroup -g 1001 -S nodejs && \
    adduser -S nodejs -u 1001
USER nodejs
```

